02:45.598 --> 02:48.499
- Is that for us?
- No, it's for you.

02:48.601 --> 02:50.535
- What is that?
- A mantrap.

02:50.670 --> 02:53.571
They used to use it
for catching poachers.

02:53.673 --> 02:55.368
Hello, Amy.

02:55.475 --> 02:57.841
- Hello, Charlie.
- Where do we put it, Mr. Sumner?

02:57.944 --> 03:01.004
- Oh. Here in the back.
- Oh, it's heavy, Mr. Sumner.

03:01.114 --> 03:03.981
I'm surprised
you still remember me.

03:04.083 --> 03:05.983
Where do we put it, Amy?

03:06.085 --> 03:08.986
Anywhere you want.
It's your birthday present.

03:09.088 --> 03:11.648
- Happy birthday.
- Thank you.

03:11.758 --> 03:14.192
- Don't scratch it.
- Why are you surprised?

03:14.294 --> 03:17.354
- How long has it been, Charlie?
- Three summer holidays in six years.

03:19.432 --> 03:22.367
David, this is an old
friend of mine, Charlie Venner.

03:22.468 --> 03:24.368
My husband, David Sumner.

03:24.470 --> 03:26.370
- Mr. Venner.
- Please call me Charlie.

03:26.472 --> 03:28.736
You work around here?

03:28.841 --> 03:30.604
Sometimes.

03:30.710 --> 03:33.110
- Will you give me a hand, please?
- Yeah.

03:33.213 --> 03:35.613
- David's a mathematician.
- What are you going to catch?

03:35.715 --> 03:38.343
- Peace and quiet.
- Oh, an arithmetic teacher.

03:38.451 --> 03:39.850
- Well, uh--
- No.

03:39.953 --> 03:41.853
He's writing a book...

03:41.955 --> 03:44.685
on the computer analysis
of the celestial--

03:44.791 --> 03:47.521
Good try. Here, why don't you
put this in the trunk, Amy.

03:47.660 --> 03:49.560
Let me.

03:55.034 --> 03:58.333
Maybe, um, Charlie could
help us with the garage, David.

03:58.438 --> 04:01.032
Yeah, that's a good idea.
This fellow Norman, uh--

04:01.140 --> 04:03.370
- Scutt.
- Yes.

04:03.476 --> 04:08.038
- He's, uh, taking forever.
- Me and Bobby'll do it for you, Mr. Sumner.

04:08.147 --> 04:11.446
Me and my cousin Bertie will be out
tomorrow. We'll get it up for you.

04:11.551 --> 04:13.451
Yes? How much?

04:13.553 --> 04:17.045
- Oh, reasonable.
- Okay, thank you.

04:17.156 --> 04:19.420
- We're at--
- Back at Trencher's farm.

04:19.524 --> 04:21.390
We'll be there, sir.

04:22.695 --> 04:24.595
Good. Good.

04:30.903 --> 04:32.803
Where are you going?

04:32.905 --> 04:34.497
David?

04:34.607 --> 04:37.269
- Where are you going?
- Cigarettes.

04:38.878 --> 04:41.574
Okay.

04:45.285 --> 04:48.686
Uh, a couple of packs of
any American cigarettes, please.

04:48.788 --> 04:51.188
- Time, gentlemen, please.

04:51.291 --> 04:53.782
Finish your drinkin', gentlemen.
Let me have your glasses.

05:09.175 --> 05:11.075
Henry Niles.

05:11.177 --> 05:13.645
I thought he was to be put away.

05:13.746 --> 05:17.409
Oh, we can take care
of our own here. Usually do.

05:24.791 --> 05:27.021
Remember when
I took care of you, Amy?

05:33.933 --> 05:36.697
But you didn't.
Remember?

05:38.971 --> 05:42.236
There was once a time,
Mrs. Sumner...

05:42.342 --> 05:45.800
when you were ready
to beg me for it.

05:45.912 --> 05:47.812
Take your hands off me.

06:10.002 --> 06:12.903
Come on, gentlemen. Drink up.
Let me have your glasses, please.

06:13.005 --> 06:14.973
Bloody early, Harry.

06:20.480 --> 06:22.243
Harry...

06:23.383 --> 06:26.250
I think I should have another pint.

06:34.494 --> 06:36.394
Sorry about my uncle, Harry.

06:36.496 --> 06:38.396
I think he's a bit taken with drink.

06:38.498 --> 06:40.398
Oh.

06:40.500 --> 06:43.731
I do beg your pardon,
Mr. Harry Ware.

06:43.836 --> 06:48.034
- I'll pay for the American gentlemen's cigarettes.
- Oh, no, that's okay, I--

06:48.141 --> 06:50.769
That's all right.
I got it, sir.

06:50.877 --> 06:52.777
Garage coming along?

06:52.879 --> 06:54.779
Norman fixing it up all right?

06:54.881 --> 06:56.644
Yeah.

06:59.886 --> 07:01.717
And I'll pay for the glass.

07:01.821 --> 07:05.518
And I'll even pay for the little bit of
plaster to put on your bleedin' finger.

07:05.625 --> 07:09.857
But I do think I should have
another pint to take me home.

07:09.996 --> 07:12.362
The bar's closed, Tom.

07:12.465 --> 07:14.365
- Come on, Tom.
- Oh.

07:14.467 --> 07:17.061
It is, is it?

07:17.170 --> 07:19.468
We'll see about that.!

07:19.572 --> 07:22.973
- Take it easy, old man!
- Old man, you say?

07:44.063 --> 07:45.963
All right, Tom.

07:46.065 --> 07:47.862
You've had your fun.

07:47.967 --> 07:49.867
Pay the man and leave.

07:51.103 --> 07:53.003
Ah.

07:56.375 --> 07:59.139
Oh.

07:59.245 --> 08:02.408
I do beg your pardon,
Mr. Magistrate.

08:06.686 --> 08:09.416
But what I am, I am.

08:09.522 --> 08:11.422
What's the damage, Harry?

08:11.524 --> 08:13.151
Call it a quid, Tom.

08:13.259 --> 08:15.693
Let's call it, uh...

08:15.795 --> 08:17.695
30 bob.

08:19.465 --> 08:22.366
Will that do then, eh, Major?

08:22.468 --> 08:24.436
Go home, Tom, will you...

08:24.537 --> 08:27.028
or you'll be up before me
on a fresh charge.

08:34.246 --> 08:36.477
Come on, lads.
Work to be done.

08:37.683 --> 08:40.549
- See you tonight, Harry.
- All right, Tom.

08:47.627 --> 08:49.527
I showed him, eh, lads?

08:54.333 --> 08:56.233
Uh, they're paid for, sir.

08:59.138 --> 09:01.003
They are now.

09:24.463 --> 09:27.591
- Stupid cow!
- Get off.

09:27.700 --> 09:30.362
What was that about?

09:35.308 --> 09:38.209
Who was that big guy
with the beard?

09:38.311 --> 09:40.871
Why?

09:40.980 --> 09:43.881
Is he any relation
to your friend Charlie?

09:43.983 --> 09:45.883
Yes.

10:03.736 --> 10:07.069
How well do you know
this fellow Venner?

10:08.474 --> 10:10.374
Stop teasing.

10:10.476 --> 10:12.842
- Did you ever go out with him?
-Stop.

10:12.945 --> 10:15.345
- Hmm?
- Leave me alone! Stop it!

10:15.448 --> 10:17.848
Stop.

10:17.950 --> 10:19.850
- Tell me.
- I'll stop the car.

10:19.952 --> 10:22.147
I just want to know.
Tell me.

10:23.055 --> 10:24.989
Stop. I'm telling you.

10:25.091 --> 10:27.651
- You asked for it.
- Okay.

10:27.793 --> 10:29.693
All right, drive the car-- Ooh!

10:29.795 --> 10:31.592
Ooh! Ooh!

10:31.697 --> 10:33.562
You asked for it!
Chicken!

10:33.666 --> 10:36.464
- You're nuts!
- You're terrible! You're wicked!

10:36.569 --> 10:40.300
Oh, by the way--

10:40.406 --> 10:42.966
- Yeah?
- Venner did try to get fresh once.

10:43.075 --> 10:45.635
Yeah? So?

10:45.745 --> 10:49.237
Nothing happened.!
# Ba-bum #

10:49.348 --> 10:52.681
# Ba-ba-bah-bum
Ba-ba, ba-bum #

11:19.512 --> 11:21.412
Hi.

11:23.816 --> 11:25.716
You'll have some help tomorrow.

11:25.818 --> 11:31.051
Charles Venner and his cousin
are coming to help finish the garage.

11:31.157 --> 11:33.717
We'll have the garage finished
before Chris gets the rats out.

11:34.894 --> 11:36.657
- Hello, miss.
- Chris?

11:36.796 --> 11:38.423
Yeah, Chris.

11:39.965 --> 11:43.457
Oh,yes. Mr. Cawsey.
The rat man.

11:43.569 --> 11:45.469
- Want help with this, sir?
- Yes.

11:47.006 --> 11:49.236
It's a real antique, sir.

11:49.341 --> 11:52.640
- Rare, they are.
- My wife is a collector.

11:52.745 --> 11:54.645
But I end up with them.

11:54.747 --> 11:57.648
I find it's a bit large
for my prey, sir.

11:57.750 --> 11:59.775
- Won't do at all.
- Don't count on it.

11:59.885 --> 12:01.978
- Do you like it here, sir?
- Very much.

12:02.088 --> 12:04.989
I hear it's pretty rough
in the States, sir.

12:05.091 --> 12:06.991
Have you seen some of it, sir?

12:07.093 --> 12:09.891
Bombin', riotin', snipin',
shootin' the blacks?

12:10.029 --> 12:11.929
Can't walk down the streets, they say.

12:12.031 --> 12:14.932
Was you involved in it, sir?
I mean, did you take part?

12:15.034 --> 12:16.695
See anybody get knifed?

12:16.802 --> 12:19.270
Just between commercials.

12:20.973 --> 12:22.907
Wanna put that down there?

12:25.010 --> 12:28.446
No, I'm just glad I'm here
where it's, uh, quiet...

12:28.547 --> 12:33.644
and you can breathe fresh air
and drink water that doesn't
have to come out of a bottle.

12:33.753 --> 12:36.916
It isn't water that I drink
out of a bottle, sir.

12:40.926 --> 12:43.986
Those two fellows will be up
to help you tomorrow.

12:53.405 --> 12:53.803
Kitty.!

12:55.608 --> 12:58.509
- You gonna have a crack at her, Norman?
- No.

12:58.611 --> 13:00.943
Ten months inside
is enough for me.

13:02.181 --> 13:04.479
- They got anything worth taking?
- Nope.

13:06.752 --> 13:08.652
Except, uh...

13:08.754 --> 13:11.154
these.

13:11.257 --> 13:13.157
- You bloody fool.
- It was nothing.

13:13.292 --> 13:15.487
She's got a dozen or more.

13:15.628 --> 13:18.529
Full of perfume.

13:20.432 --> 13:22.332
You like my trophy?

13:22.434 --> 13:24.334
Bugger your trophy.

13:24.436 --> 13:26.836
I want what was in 'em.

13:30.442 --> 13:33.343
I could do with
some of that too, Normie.

13:35.114 --> 13:37.014
Charlie Venner.

13:37.116 --> 13:39.516
He had some of it years ago...

13:39.618 --> 13:41.609
when she was here with her father.

13:41.720 --> 13:43.620
Venner's a bloody liar...

13:43.722 --> 13:45.622
and so are you.

13:49.428 --> 13:52.488
# Tell her, smell her
Lock her in the cellar #

13:52.631 --> 13:54.531
Kitty, kitty.
Where are you?

13:55.901 --> 13:57.801
Kitty.

14:00.973 --> 14:02.873
Kitty, kitty.

14:05.411 --> 14:07.208
Kitty, kitty.

14:07.313 --> 14:09.781
Kitty, kitty, kitty.

14:09.882 --> 14:12.442
Want a drink?

14:12.551 --> 14:14.576
I can't find the cat.

14:14.687 --> 14:16.587
Doesn't answer my call.

14:17.756 --> 14:20.281
Do I?

14:20.392 --> 14:22.326
You'd better.

14:32.104 --> 14:34.504
Why did you hire
Charlie Venner?

14:36.342 --> 14:38.742
I didn't. You did.

14:38.844 --> 14:40.744
Kitty.

14:40.846 --> 14:43.246
If she's in my study,
I'll kill her.

14:48.821 --> 14:50.721
What?

14:51.824 --> 14:53.758
Nothing.

15:14.146 --> 15:16.137
That your daddy's chair?

15:19.285 --> 15:21.753
Every chair is my daddy's chair.

15:36.702 --> 15:38.567
I'm glad we came.

15:44.476 --> 15:46.569
- What are you doing?
- Kiss me.

15:46.679 --> 15:48.909
Mmm.

15:51.016 --> 15:53.416
- You're an animal.
- Mm-mmm.

15:59.358 --> 16:02.850
Why'd you take my heater
out of the study?

16:04.997 --> 16:07.488
Because it's going upstairs.

16:07.633 --> 16:09.533
What happened?

16:13.906 --> 16:15.806
It's not going upstairs.

16:15.908 --> 16:17.671
It's freezing in there.

16:26.218 --> 16:28.345
Hello.

16:28.454 --> 16:30.854
I can see you're working at top speed.

16:30.956 --> 16:33.754
Is he in there studying?

16:35.894 --> 16:38.328
You'd better do something.

16:38.464 --> 16:41.365
- My husband will think all Englishmen are lazy.
- Let me help.

16:42.468 --> 16:44.129
Hey!

16:55.881 --> 16:59.180
Yeah, come on over here. This way.

17:00.285 --> 17:02.310
Watch your fingers, Chris.

17:11.463 --> 17:13.829
What was so funny with them?

17:16.268 --> 17:18.998
They just think
you're strange.

17:21.006 --> 17:22.973
Why, because I'm American?

17:24.476 --> 17:26.944
Mmm, no. No.

17:27.046 --> 17:29.139
Just strange.

17:32.818 --> 17:34.718
Do you think I'm strange?

17:36.455 --> 17:38.355
Occasionally.

17:41.126 --> 17:43.526
You act like you're 1 4.

17:45.864 --> 17:47.764
I am.

17:48.901 --> 17:50.801
Wanna try for 1 2?

17:53.672 --> 17:56.266
How about eight?
I freak out for eight-year-olds.

18:07.719 --> 18:10.847
- David?
- Huh?

18:10.956 --> 18:13.356
Will you please
get some lettuce?

18:14.993 --> 18:16.893
Okay.

18:19.098 --> 18:21.498
Oh, and fix
the damned toaster.

18:31.844 --> 18:34.745
What does she think
I'm doing here, playing games?

18:34.847 --> 18:36.747
What is this,
grammar school?

18:36.849 --> 18:38.749
Jesus Christ.

18:51.196 --> 18:53.596
Uh, we're leavin' now,
Mr. Sumner.

18:53.699 --> 18:56.532
- Mr. Riddaway be givin' us a lift.
- Fine.

18:57.936 --> 19:00.404
Oh, I was just sayin'
to your missus...

19:00.506 --> 19:04.272
that in a funny sort of way I feel
closer to rats than I do to people.

19:04.376 --> 19:07.812
Even though I kill 'em for a living.
Their dying is my living.

19:11.316 --> 19:14.547
Smell a rat, see a rat, kill a rat.
That's me, Chris Cawsey.

19:14.653 --> 19:18.054
I'd be lost without 'em.
It's true. I tell you straight.

19:18.157 --> 19:21.126
Cleverest thing you ever see
around these parts is a rat.

19:21.260 --> 19:23.660
Rats is life!

19:38.310 --> 19:40.870
Shove up,
you overgrown bastard.

19:40.979 --> 19:44.380
How's your day been?
Been up in a fat sheep, have ya?

19:46.485 --> 19:49.477
# Oh, you fluffy fleecy darlings #

19:49.588 --> 19:51.488
# You with the dark brown eyes #

19:51.590 --> 19:53.990
David?

19:54.092 --> 19:56.652
David.!

19:56.795 --> 19:58.820
Dinner's ready.!

20:00.032 --> 20:01.932
Did you hear me?

20:10.475 --> 20:13.171
- Hello, Major.
- Evening, Major.

20:13.278 --> 20:16.543
- Evening. - Will you be having
a pint with me then, Major?

20:16.648 --> 20:18.548
Not tonight.
I'll buy my own.

20:20.018 --> 20:21.952
Otherwise
we'd never get out of here.

20:22.054 --> 20:23.954
You know that.

20:24.056 --> 20:25.614
Yes, I do know that.

20:26.892 --> 20:29.019
Thanks, Harry.

20:29.161 --> 20:31.391
Excellent.

20:33.265 --> 20:35.563
- John.
- Evening, sir.

20:36.902 --> 20:38.802
- Fancy a game?
- Aye.

20:38.904 --> 20:40.804
- Evening, Harry.
- Evening.

20:43.375 --> 20:45.639
John Niles, come here to me.

20:45.744 --> 20:49.771
- Is this for a drink, Tom?
- No, this is for the truth.

20:51.049 --> 20:52.949
Your brother.

20:53.051 --> 20:54.951
Been hangin' around
the girls again.

20:55.053 --> 20:58.750
You'd better keep a closer watch,
or we'll be puttin' him away.

21:00.225 --> 21:02.420
It's all right, Pa.

21:02.561 --> 21:04.791
He's only throwing the ball
to 'em a little.

21:04.930 --> 21:06.830
A little's too much
for that sod.

21:06.932 --> 21:08.729
Watch your tongue, Norman.

21:08.834 --> 21:11.564
I'll watch nothin'
except my own ways.

21:11.670 --> 21:14.571
You watch your brother,
or I'll do it for you.

21:14.673 --> 21:17.471
If he ever makes
a mistake again in any way...

21:17.576 --> 21:20.477
I'll be the first
to have him put away.

21:23.715 --> 21:27.617
David.! You've been at it for hours.!

21:33.158 --> 21:35.058
Aah!

21:35.193 --> 21:38.128
- Gave me a fright, you did.
- You watching him, are you?

21:38.230 --> 21:40.630
Just lookin'.

21:43.969 --> 21:45.869
Do you fancy him?

21:48.273 --> 21:50.173
He's sweet, I think.

22:18.303 --> 22:20.203
Want anything?

22:27.813 --> 22:29.713
Want a tomato?

22:29.815 --> 22:32.477
No, thanks.

22:32.584 --> 22:34.984
Want a grapefruit?

22:54.573 --> 22:56.973
- Hey, hey.
- Your move.

22:57.075 --> 23:00.044
Okay.

23:05.517 --> 23:07.883
Check.

23:07.986 --> 23:11.387
- No, thank you.
- Mm-hmm, mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

23:11.490 --> 23:13.981
''This move now...

23:14.092 --> 23:17.528
''puts black into
a desperate plight...

23:17.662 --> 23:21.723
''with no possibility of mobilizing
his disorganized pieces.

23:21.867 --> 23:24.461
''Therefore, he begins
to return material...

23:24.569 --> 23:28.369
''to make progress
in developing at any price.

23:28.473 --> 23:32.500
Two pawns down,
white can conveniently--''

23:32.611 --> 23:37.480
Hey, I bet I can undress,
do my exercises and get into bed
before you make your next move.

23:37.582 --> 23:39.709
- Is it a deal?
- You're on.

23:41.553 --> 23:44.454
- Ah! No cheating.
- I'm not cheating.

23:54.099 --> 23:56.260
Shh, David.

23:59.905 --> 24:03.204
Aha! I have it.

24:06.311 --> 24:09.212
No, no, no, David,
just a minute.

24:09.314 --> 24:11.214
You're supposed to do a hundred.

24:11.316 --> 24:13.876
I did a hundred. I counted
by binary numbers. Make your move.

24:13.985 --> 24:15.885
- Binary numbers.
- Make your move.

24:15.987 --> 24:17.887
- Wait a minute.
- Come on.

24:22.561 --> 24:24.961
- What about that one there?
- No.

24:29.568 --> 24:32.469
- Uh--
- It's difficult, isn't it?

24:32.571 --> 24:34.471
Terribly.

24:34.573 --> 24:37.303
Just a minute.

24:37.409 --> 24:39.741
I think I have it.

24:39.845 --> 24:42.541
Um--

24:42.647 --> 24:44.842
Ooh.

24:46.051 --> 24:47.951
That puts you in.

25:08.807 --> 25:11.037
- Jesus!
- What are you doing?

25:11.142 --> 25:14.043
I gotta get my watch off.
You're an animal.

25:18.283 --> 25:20.717
Oh, for Christ's sake.

25:20.819 --> 25:22.719
I'm just setting the alarm.

25:30.128 --> 25:32.028
Are you finished?

25:37.269 --> 25:40.261
- Wait a minute.
- Oh, no. What now?

25:42.007 --> 25:43.907
David.

25:44.009 --> 25:46.773
David, what are you
doing down there?

25:46.878 --> 25:50.041
- Looking for a chess piece.
- What are you doing?

25:51.883 --> 25:53.783
Take a look.

25:56.388 --> 25:59.789
- Whoa. Did you find it?
- No, not that.

25:59.891 --> 26:02.860
Wait a minute.
Let me give you a hand.

26:02.994 --> 26:05.087
Aah.!

26:05.230 --> 26:07.596
David, no.!

26:07.699 --> 26:10.862
- No, wait! Wait a minute!
- You see it? Huh?

26:10.969 --> 26:13.164
- No, I didn't find it.
- I think it's a rook.

26:13.271 --> 26:16.604
No.! Aah.! No.!

26:16.708 --> 26:19.541
Mmm.! I love you.!

26:23.815 --> 26:25.715
I never cheat.

27:00.285 --> 27:02.515
Look, Amy,
don't play games with me.

27:04.856 --> 27:06.756
I've got a lot on my mind.

27:06.858 --> 27:09.258
You're not being fair.
I'm just trying to help.

27:16.067 --> 27:18.627
If you want to help,
then get your friends to finish.

27:18.737 --> 27:22.639
Get the garage makers and the
rat catchers-- Get them all to finish!

27:22.741 --> 27:26.006
- Oh.
- A-And fix the toilet
and clean up the kitchen.

27:26.111 --> 27:28.011
That would be a terrific help!

27:31.750 --> 27:35.083
I love you, Amy,
but I want you to leave me alone.

27:43.261 --> 27:45.161
Okay.

27:46.331 --> 27:49.198
I'll leave you alone
with your blackboard.

28:20.832 --> 28:22.766
Don't play games with me.

28:24.969 --> 28:26.869
No.

28:26.971 --> 28:29.337
Don't do it, Amy.

29:25.630 --> 29:28.531
They were practically licking my body.

