No!

01:00:27.056 --> 01:00:30.423
No.

01:00:42.939 --> 01:00:44.839
Amy!

01:01:25.581 --> 01:01:27.742
N-No.

01:02:20.870 --> 01:02:22.770
Easy.

01:02:59.542 --> 01:03:01.476
I'm sorry, Amy.

01:03:01.577 --> 01:03:03.477
I'm sorry.

01:03:03.579 --> 01:03:05.479
Hold me.

01:03:07.950 --> 01:03:10.077
Hold me.

01:05:10.006 --> 01:05:12.975
No.

01:05:16.646 --> 01:05:19.979
No.! No.! No.!

01:07:21.203 --> 01:07:23.501
Why didn't you open the closet?

01:07:23.606 --> 01:07:25.836
We don't have any more cats.

01:07:33.282 --> 01:07:36.274
I'm firing Venner
and Scutt tomorrow.

01:07:37.653 --> 01:07:39.587
Hooray for you, tiger.

01:07:44.894 --> 01:07:46.794
What for?

01:07:50.232 --> 01:07:53.599
Because they stuck it to me
on the moor today.

01:07:53.702 --> 01:07:57.160
They also serve
who sit at home and wait.

01:07:58.707 --> 01:08:00.868
What?

01:08:00.976 --> 01:08:03.501
Nothing. If you'd have said
something to them ages ago...

01:08:03.612 --> 01:08:05.944
-about the cat, this would
never have happened.
- Easy.

01:08:06.048 --> 01:08:08.073
- None of it.
- Easy, easy.

01:08:08.184 --> 01:08:10.516
I was going to say something
until you pulled that childish stunt...

01:08:10.619 --> 01:08:13.349
and ruined any chance
I had of finding out.

01:08:13.456 --> 01:08:15.356
- David, I didn't--
- I didn't finish.

01:08:15.458 --> 01:08:18.256
- You pushed me, and you don't do
any good by pushing.
- I didn't.

01:08:24.500 --> 01:08:27.401
When are you ever gonna
learn about growing up, huh?

01:08:29.205 --> 01:08:31.104
I'm trying to.

01:08:31.207 --> 01:08:33.265
Well, you're a little late.

01:08:36.412 --> 01:08:40.644
Why didn't you ask him
instead of making me look like
an idiot with that bowl of milk?

01:08:40.749 --> 01:08:43.149
You're a coward.

01:08:45.386 --> 01:08:47.617
- No, I'm not.
-And I'm a coward.

01:08:48.890 --> 01:08:50.791
Plain and simple.

01:08:50.926 --> 01:08:53.053
No, I'm not.

01:08:53.194 --> 01:08:57.096
I don't blame you
for hiding in your study.

01:08:57.198 --> 01:08:59.099
I don't--

01:08:59.201 --> 01:09:01.362
I don't want to
hide there with you.

01:09:03.037 --> 01:09:07.475
I-- I can't anymore.

01:09:14.250 --> 01:09:16.149
Okay.

01:09:19.087 --> 01:09:21.818
Easy, easy, easy.

01:09:33.903 --> 01:09:36.736
- You're fired, all of you.
- I beg your pardon, sir?

01:09:36.839 --> 01:09:39.273
I've noted the hours
that you've worked...

01:09:39.375 --> 01:09:43.072
and I've deducted...
the-the time wasted.

01:09:43.179 --> 01:09:46.580
- Here. It's all here.
- Why, sir? Why are we fired?

01:09:46.682 --> 01:09:48.979
We may not work the way
you like to work, sir--

01:09:49.084 --> 01:09:51.951
- Listen to me.
- Sir, I mean, why?

01:09:52.054 --> 01:09:55.717
You're fired because I don't want you
around. I want you to leave. Right now.

01:09:55.824 --> 01:09:58.418
- Is that clear?
- We've been working all the time, sir.

01:09:58.561 --> 01:10:00.654
Clear enough, sir.

01:10:30.626 --> 01:10:32.560
- Norman.
- Huh?

01:10:32.661 --> 01:10:35.562
That's a nice way
to treat people.

01:11:33.555 --> 01:11:36.888
We're due at the church hall at 8:00.

01:12:09.725 --> 01:12:13.183
I'd like you
to meet Amy and David Sumner.

01:12:13.329 --> 01:12:16.526
- Hello. Nice to meet you. My husband.
- Hello, Mr. Sumner.

01:12:16.632 --> 01:12:18.566
Hello, Amy.
Nice of you to come.

01:12:18.667 --> 01:12:21.795
I'll show you to your seats.

01:12:21.904 --> 01:12:24.737
Hello, Reverend.
How have you been?

01:12:40.022 --> 01:12:41.956
- Please sit here.
- Thank you.

01:12:42.057 --> 01:12:44.491
- I think she'll be able
to see okay from here.
- That's fine.

01:12:57.005 --> 01:12:59.974
Would you care for a drink?

01:13:01.443 --> 01:13:03.638
All right. Thank you.

01:13:16.358 --> 01:13:19.327
I hope you enjoy the show.

01:13:19.428 --> 01:13:21.919
Thank you.

01:13:22.064 --> 01:13:24.464
Be brave.

01:13:38.947 --> 01:13:43.441
Evening, ladies and gentlemen...

01:13:47.923 --> 01:13:49.857
and welcome to our
annual social gathering.

01:13:49.958 --> 01:13:53.257
It's nice to see again
all the old familiar faces.

01:13:53.395 --> 01:13:55.386
And the not-so-old,
indeed, as well.

01:13:55.531 --> 01:13:59.023
To begin the evening, we have
our very own Reverend Barnard Hood.

01:13:59.168 --> 01:14:02.569
Your vicar,
ladies and gentlemen.

01:14:02.671 --> 01:14:07.870
Thank you very much.
And now, ladies and gentlemen,
for my famous newspaper trick.

01:14:07.976 --> 01:14:10.001
Tore it up last year, Barny!

01:14:10.112 --> 01:14:13.809
Yes, and I might well
next year, too, Tom.

01:14:17.119 --> 01:14:19.679
Here we are, ladies and gentlemen--
a very simple trick.

01:14:19.788 --> 01:14:22.655
I simply tear a piece
of newspaper down the center so.

01:14:22.758 --> 01:14:26.421
Tear it again.
Fold it towards me.

01:14:26.562 --> 01:14:28.894
Music, please.

01:14:28.997 --> 01:14:33.730
Open it up very carefully.
Tear it again.

01:14:33.836 --> 01:14:36.862
There we are.
Roll it towards me again.

01:14:36.972 --> 01:14:39.202
- You enjoy this, Mrs.Johnson?
- Yes, Vicar.

01:14:39.308 --> 01:14:42.505
It is a good trick, isn't it? I do it
in front of the mirror every night.

01:14:42.611 --> 01:14:44.841
And we begin to open up.

01:14:44.947 --> 01:14:47.609
- I always enjoy doing this.
It gives me a chance to...
- Hello, David.

01:14:47.716 --> 01:14:49.149
catch up with my reading.

01:14:49.251 --> 01:14:51.151
Hi.

01:14:54.156 --> 01:14:56.351
You want a smoke?

01:14:56.458 --> 01:15:00.656
And I find that
it hasn't been torn at all.

01:15:00.796 --> 01:15:03.629
- No. - What?
- Don't smoke in here.

01:15:03.732 --> 01:15:06.223
And you'll also find that
that one isn't torn either.

01:15:06.368 --> 01:15:09.303
Sorry about that, ladies and gentlemen.

01:15:09.404 --> 01:15:12.066
But I think
you'll probably find that...

01:15:12.174 --> 01:15:14.870
it hasn't been torn at all.

01:15:19.581 --> 01:15:23.278
- Hello, Henry.
- Hello.

01:15:25.554 --> 01:15:29.012
I'd like to go for a walk.

01:15:29.124 --> 01:15:32.252
- Will you take my arm?
- Now, ladies and gentlemen...

01:15:32.394 --> 01:15:34.589
for my piece de resistance...

01:15:34.730 --> 01:15:38.222
I now present to you an empty glass.

01:15:38.367 --> 01:15:40.767
I am now going to fill
this glass with milk.

01:15:40.869 --> 01:15:43.633
Would it work better
with whiskey, vicar?

01:15:43.739 --> 01:15:45.934
- Nothing works better with whiskey.
- I do.

01:15:46.041 --> 01:15:48.134
You've never worked
in your life, Tom.

01:15:52.648 --> 01:15:57.108
Now, ladies and gentlemen,
I take the lid off my cocoa tin.

01:15:57.219 --> 01:16:01.349
And very carefully now,
I place the glass...

01:16:01.456 --> 01:16:04.983
into the tin
and replace the lid.

01:16:05.127 --> 01:16:08.619
I take up my wand
and I utter the magic words--

01:16:15.237 --> 01:16:17.569
What do we find in the tin...

01:16:17.673 --> 01:16:21.040
but one complete...

01:16:21.143 --> 01:16:23.134
glass of milk.

01:16:23.245 --> 01:16:27.238
- Yea.!
- Good old Barny!

01:16:27.349 --> 01:16:30.978
If I could convert you
to this, Tom, that would be a miracle.

01:16:35.190 --> 01:16:38.216
Thank you very much.
Thank you. Major.

01:16:38.360 --> 01:16:41.454
The next item on this evening's
program, ladies and gentlemen...

01:16:41.597 --> 01:16:44.998
- You want to go?
- Yeah.

01:16:45.100 --> 01:16:49.002
...who will sing for you the aria
Caranome from the opera Rigoletto.

01:17:27.476 --> 01:17:30.104
Dad?
It's Janice.

01:17:30.212 --> 01:17:33.375
She made off to the yard.
Then she went walking with Henry Niles.

01:17:33.482 --> 01:17:35.712
He was holding her, Dad.
Touching her.

01:17:35.817 --> 01:17:38.786
John Niles.

01:17:38.887 --> 01:17:41.617
What's the matter, Tom?

01:17:49.031 --> 01:17:51.397
Come with me.

01:17:58.373 --> 01:18:01.001
All over her, he was.
Touching her.

01:18:02.811 --> 01:18:05.746
Had his hands all over her.

01:18:20.395 --> 01:18:22.363
Don't be afraid, Henry.

01:18:22.497 --> 01:18:24.397
- I'll find him.
- No.

01:18:24.499 --> 01:18:26.467
Let the boys find Janice.
The rest can wait.

01:18:29.337 --> 01:18:31.635
Have you ever kissed
anyone, Henry?

01:18:31.740 --> 01:18:34.106
No.

01:18:34.209 --> 01:18:37.576
Get your mates to find her. I'll be
waiting in the pub. Get all of them!

01:18:39.047 --> 01:18:41.948
Would you like to kiss me?

01:18:52.994 --> 01:18:55.019
Go on. Find him!

01:18:56.832 --> 01:18:59.733
Would you now all please stand?

01:19:17.719 --> 01:19:22.053
As these lights are
extinguished in our eyes...

01:19:23.391 --> 01:19:28.090
and also in the presence of God,
the Blessed Virgin...

01:19:28.230 --> 01:19:30.460
and all the saints--

01:19:35.003 --> 01:19:39.736
Deliver unto the devil
a punishment with eternal fire.

01:19:41.109 --> 01:19:44.442
Dwell without him...

01:19:44.546 --> 01:19:48.676
unless ye repent.

01:19:48.784 --> 01:19:51.412
-Janice?
-Janice.!

01:19:51.520 --> 01:19:54.512
- Amen.
- Amen.

01:19:54.623 --> 01:19:58.525
- I have to go.
- No. No, they might hurt you.

01:20:05.433 --> 01:20:07.401
- Janice.!
- Come here.!

01:20:07.536 --> 01:20:10.699
- Where are you,Janice?
- Henry.!

01:20:12.073 --> 01:20:14.837
Janice.!

01:20:27.289 --> 01:20:30.258
We don't know where she is.
We looked the whole town!

01:20:30.358 --> 01:20:33.225
- Keep looking.
- The fog's coming down.

01:20:33.328 --> 01:20:36.695
Did you try the lorries and such,
parked outside the meeting house?

01:20:36.798 --> 01:20:38.823
- Then do it!
- I'll go with him, Pa.

01:20:38.967 --> 01:20:41.800
- Janice?
- Janice.!

01:20:43.872 --> 01:20:46.340
Janice.!

01:21:05.126 --> 01:21:07.856
We're almost home now.

01:21:14.803 --> 01:21:17.067
Can I help?

01:21:20.141 --> 01:21:22.041
David!

01:21:25.914 --> 01:21:28.747
Jesus! I couldn't stop.

01:21:28.850 --> 01:21:32.149
- Oh, God, David.!
- Easy.

01:21:33.855 --> 01:21:36.187
Okay. Get the keys.

01:21:36.291 --> 01:21:38.521
Easy. Easy.

01:21:41.429 --> 01:21:44.830
-
-
David,you know it's Henry Niles?

01:21:44.933 --> 01:21:46.833
I don't want him here.

01:21:46.935 --> 01:21:49.665
He's hurt.

01:21:49.771 --> 01:21:52.831
I don't want him in my house.

01:21:52.941 --> 01:21:56.206
Fine. You get upstairs.
You go to bed.

01:21:56.311 --> 01:21:59.144
Take a bath.
You just get out of here.

01:22:01.082 --> 01:22:04.449
He'll stay until the doctor comes.

01:22:04.552 --> 01:22:07.453
What do you mean,
you don't want him in your house?

01:22:17.866 --> 01:22:20.801
- David, did you get anyone?
- No.!

01:22:20.936 --> 01:22:24.804
I tried the doctor. He's not home,
and the consul's not either.

01:22:24.906 --> 01:22:29.138
Nobody answers.
I'm calling the pub.

01:22:41.923 --> 01:22:45.256
- Wakely Arms.
- Hello, this is David Sumner.

01:22:46.561 --> 01:22:49.189
No. No, he ain't.

01:22:49.331 --> 01:22:53.290
Oh. Well, when he comes in,
tell him to call Trencher's Farm.

01:22:53.435 --> 01:22:56.802
I've got Henry Niles here.

01:22:56.905 --> 01:22:58.873
Right.

01:22:58.974 --> 01:23:01.272
It was the American,
looking for Allsopp.

01:23:01.376 --> 01:23:04.140
He hit Henry Niles with his car.

01:23:04.245 --> 01:23:06.577
He's got him up at Trencher's.

01:23:10.085 --> 01:23:12.645
Bottle.

01:23:12.754 --> 01:23:14.654
And another.

01:23:52.727 --> 01:23:55.525
Let Norman and me go in, Tom.

01:23:55.630 --> 01:23:57.530
We know the American.

01:23:57.632 --> 01:24:01.534
- I want to know where myJanice is.
- We'll find out, Tom.

01:24:01.669 --> 01:24:04.263
Riddaway will stay with you, Tom.

01:24:04.372 --> 01:24:06.863
That I will.

01:24:17.919 --> 01:24:21.184
- You have Henry Niles in there?
- Wait a minute. Is the doctor with you?

01:24:21.289 --> 01:24:23.951
- We want to see Niles.
- Why? What's the matter?

01:24:25.593 --> 01:24:27.788
Wake up!

01:24:27.929 --> 01:24:30.864
- Wake up!
- Don't try to kid us
you're sleeping. Come on.!

01:24:30.965 --> 01:24:33.559
- Hey, wait a minute, now.
- Come on! Come on!

01:24:33.668 --> 01:24:35.829
He's hurt.
He could have a broken rib.

01:24:35.937 --> 01:24:37.837
Oh. Sorry, sir.

01:24:39.707 --> 01:24:43.666
He'll have more than a broken rib if he
doesn't tell us whereJanice Hedden is.

01:24:43.778 --> 01:24:46.576
- What aboutJanice Hedden?
- Took her, he did.

01:24:46.681 --> 01:24:48.808
What have you done with Janice Hedden,
you dirty pervert?

01:24:48.917 --> 01:24:51.750
Lookee here. He played
his filthy tricks on Janice Hedden.

01:24:51.853 --> 01:24:54.014
He took her, and he was seen
with his hands on her body.

01:24:54.122 --> 01:24:56.352
She run, he run after her,
and now she's missing.

01:24:56.458 --> 01:24:58.517
- Look, I understand your concern--
- You--

01:24:58.660 --> 01:25:01.185
Don't touch him!
Don't do that.

01:25:05.433 --> 01:25:08.027
Don't lay your hands on me!

01:25:11.739 --> 01:25:15.402
It's none of your business,
and it never has been.

01:25:18.079 --> 01:25:19.979
That's fine.

01:25:22.117 --> 01:25:24.176
But you can't hit him.

01:25:24.285 --> 01:25:27.152
Listen, Mr. Sumner...

01:25:27.255 --> 01:25:30.088
we come to get
this bloody freak.

01:25:30.191 --> 01:25:32.250
And we're gonna get him...

01:25:32.393 --> 01:25:35.294
with your cooperation or without it.

01:25:35.396 --> 01:25:38.331
David, stop it.!

01:25:47.442 --> 01:25:49.569
Hey, listen.

01:25:49.677 --> 01:25:53.704
Listen, Henry, did you see
Janice Hedden tonight?

01:25:53.815 --> 01:25:56.875
Of course he did. Ain't you listenin'
to me? He did his dirty numbers on her.

01:25:56.985 --> 01:26:00.318
Just take it easy.
Henry, listen to me.

01:26:00.421 --> 01:26:05.859
Did you takeJanice Hedden out
of the meeting house tonight? Huh?

01:26:05.994 --> 01:26:08.963
Listen to me. Please.

01:26:09.097 --> 01:26:12.089
Gentlemen, he's helpless.
Look at him. He couldn't hurt a fly.

01:26:15.170 --> 01:26:18.333
You'd be better off looking for
Janice Hedden than standing around here.

01:26:18.439 --> 01:26:20.873
You know?

01:26:20.975 --> 01:26:24.035
All right. We go find Janice,
you go find the doctor.

01:26:30.785 --> 01:26:32.685
I'm not leaving him here
with my wife.

01:26:32.787 --> 01:26:34.778
- Thought you said he was helpless.
- Yeah.

01:26:34.889 --> 01:26:37.483
You wouldn't leave him alone with your
wife or your kid, if you had one.

01:26:37.592 --> 01:26:40.584
Oh, that's different, huh?

01:26:40.728 --> 01:26:43.162
Look-- Look, fella.

01:26:43.298 --> 01:26:46.267
He's staying here with me until
the doctor and the police arrive.

01:26:46.401 --> 01:26:49.564
- He's my responsibility.
- Your responsibility?

01:26:49.671 --> 01:26:52.265
- That's right.
- Why?

01:26:59.714 --> 01:27:02.478
This is my house.

01:27:05.687 --> 01:27:08.986
Okay, come on.

01:27:09.090 --> 01:27:11.024
Come on. Let's go.
Come on.

01:27:16.698 --> 01:27:18.188
The police'll be here soon.

01:27:39.087 --> 01:27:41.817
What did the bastard say?

01:27:41.923 --> 01:27:43.823
Didn't talk.

01:27:43.925 --> 01:27:46.485
Well, why didn't you make him?
That's what you went in there for!

01:27:52.267 --> 01:27:56.328
-Uh, David--
-Why don't you just go make some coffee?

01:27:59.374 --> 01:28:01.706
I want that Niles.!
I'm goin'in.

01:28:08.483 --> 01:28:11.714
- Please, David. Stop them.
- Don't worry.

01:28:16.157 --> 01:28:19.217
Solid. They can't break in.

01:28:22.864 --> 01:28:25.298
I know how they feel.

01:28:25.400 --> 01:28:28.528
I'd feel the same way if it was
my kid that was missing.

01:28:31.873 --> 01:28:35.468
Amy, go to bed, huh? Go on.

01:28:35.576 --> 01:28:37.544
I can handle this.

01:28:41.382 --> 01:28:44.840
You give me that Niles!

01:28:44.952 --> 01:28:49.355
Hey! Hey, cut it out!

01:28:49.457 --> 01:28:53.985
Listen to me. If you don't stop now,
so help me God I'll press charges!

01:29:11.479 --> 01:29:14.346
Okay, you've had your fun.

01:29:14.449 --> 01:29:16.747
I'll give you one more chance.

01:29:16.851 --> 01:29:21.515
And if you don't clear out now,
there'll be real trouble. I mean it.

01:29:29.497 --> 01:29:33.399
- Chris.!
- Come on. They're gonna cooperate now.

01:29:33.534 --> 01:29:35.365
Just go on upstairs.
Don't worry.

01:29:35.470 --> 01:29:38.337
- Where are you going?
- I'm just gonna fix the window.

01:29:49.083 --> 01:29:52.541
- Do you think we ought to
clear off, Norman? - Why?

01:29:52.653 --> 01:29:56.020
We'll get that Niles.
I tell you we will.

01:29:56.124 --> 01:29:58.957
Well, why stop then?

01:30:02.196 --> 01:30:04.790
He's got no right to live,
an animal like that.

01:30:04.932 --> 01:30:06.957
Tom, I'll run 'round,
I'll slip in the window...

01:30:07.101 --> 01:30:09.160
and get that Niles out
quick as a flash.

01:30:09.270 --> 01:30:12.103
Uh, the rest of you, kick up a row.

01:30:17.011 --> 01:30:18.911
Hey.!

01:30:21.416 --> 01:30:23.850
What the hell is wrong
with you people?

01:30:23.951 --> 01:30:27.512
It's that snipe
we're after, Mr. Sumner.

01:30:27.622 --> 01:30:31.149
- I said stay down!
- I want the lavvy.

01:30:32.560 --> 01:30:34.494
Come on.

01:30:34.629 --> 01:30:36.722
Look, you stupid Yank.

01:30:36.864 --> 01:30:39.662
Let's have Niles
before someone gets hurt!

01:30:39.767 --> 01:30:42.167
Come on. Up you go.

01:30:44.372 --> 01:30:46.738
I've had to put up
with a lot in my time.

01:30:46.841 --> 01:30:48.934
You can't leave him in there.

01:30:49.043 --> 01:30:51.637
But I draw the line at this place.

01:30:51.746 --> 01:30:54.180
No.!

01:30:54.282 --> 01:30:57.308
I'll have an answer,
or I'll have blood!

01:30:57.418 --> 01:31:00.410
Where are you going?

